---
// src/pages/services/dryer-vent-repair.astro
// Phase 3 Tier 2 (2026-04-28), neutral multi-county hub.
// title/H1/description/phone neutralized to 5 SoCal counties; merged 2-entry LocalBusiness+Service
// schema → single Service entry with inline provider (no address, no geo, no aggregateRating per
// wiki/decisions/nap-rating-policy-ssot.md); areaServed expanded 3 → 5 counties; FAQ + areas Q;
// LIMITED-SCOPE positioning preserved (appliance-side vent repair only); cleaning-specialist
// referrals kept (LA-area specialists named for LA-bound users; SoCal coverage broadened).

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;

const title = "Dryer Vent Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Same-day appliance-side dryer vent repair across LA, OC, Ventura, SB, Riverside. Transition duct + lint-trap housing + booster fan. BHGS #A49573, $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/dryer-vent-repair/";

const faqs = [
  { q: "What's the difference between dryer vent repair and dryer vent cleaning?", a: "Repair means replacing damaged or failed vent components, a crushed transition duct, a torn lint-trap housing, a failed booster fan, a broken exterior vent flap. Cleaning means removing lint accumulation from the vent pathway. These are distinct services with different equipment. Appliance-repair companies like ours handle the appliance-side repair portion (components within a few feet of the dryer) because the parts and diagnostic overlap with dryer service. Full home-vent-system cleaning, the full run from dryer to exterior termination, is done by dedicated dryer-vent-cleaning specialists with rotary-brush and vacuum equipment. If your vent is clogged with lint along a long run through walls or ceilings, that's a cleaning specialist's job, not ours. If a component is actually damaged or failed, that's our scope." },
  { q: "Which areas of Southern California do you cover?", a: "All five counties: Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. We dispatch from 8 service territories, West Hollywood (HQ), Los Angeles, Beverly Hills, Pasadena, Thousand Oaks, Irvine, Rancho Cucamonga, and Temecula, so the technician on your call is coming from the closest one. Same-day is our standard." },
  { q: "What dryer vent work does SDAR actually do?", a: "The appliance-side portion of the vent system. Specifically: transition duct replacement (the flexible or rigid 4-inch duct between the dryer back and the wall connection), lint-trap housing replacement and cleaning, appliance-side vent-collar repair, booster-fan replacement (in-duct supplemental fans some long vent runs use), and exterior vent-flap or vent-door replacement when accessible without roof or ladder work. Diagnostic also covers whether the appliance-side vent is restricted enough to affect dryer performance, sometimes the answer after a cleaning pass of the appliance-side portion is that clothes dry normally again without any part replacement needed." },
  { q: "Why don't you do full home dryer vent cleaning?", a: "Equipment and specialization. Proper home-vent-system cleaning requires rotary brushes on sectional rods (to reach long runs through walls and ceilings), high-volume vacuum systems (to contain the dislodged lint rather than blow it into the home), and safety-code knowledge for multi-story buildings and roof-cap terminations. Dryer-vent-cleaning specialists run this work daily and maintain the specialized equipment for it. We could do it mediocrely; they do it correctly. Across SoCal, established dryer-vent-cleaning companies include Dryer Vent Wizard, LA Dryer Vent, Elim Dryer Vent Cleaning, and DryerXpert in LA County, plus regional specialists serving OC, Ventura, and the Inland Empire, we'll refer you to one of them when the job is genuinely a cleaning job rather than a repair job. Appliance-side repair work is our scope and we do that part well." },
  { q: "My dryer is taking forever to dry clothes, is that a vent problem?", a: "Often yes. The most common cause of progressively longer dry times is restricted airflow from lint accumulation, either at the lint trap (quick fix you can do), at the transition duct behind the dryer (appliance-side, our scope), or somewhere further along the vent run toward the exterior (cleaning-specialist scope). Secondary causes are dryer-side: a failing heating element, a thermal fuse partially triggered, or a drum seal failure that changes airflow patterns. Our appliance-side diagnostic covers both angles, we check dryer mechanicals and appliance-side vent in one visit. If the problem is in the vent run beyond our scope, we'll tell you and refer to a cleaning specialist." },
  { q: "Is a crushed or disconnected dryer vent duct a fire hazard?", a: "Yes, and it's worth taking seriously. FEMA and NFPA data show roughly 15,000–16,000 dryer fires annually in the US, with lint buildup identified as a leading ignition factor. A crushed transition duct that restricts airflow causes the dryer to run hotter than designed as heat accumulates in the vent pathway; a disconnected duct vents lint and hot air directly into the laundry space. Both situations accelerate lint accumulation in locations where it shouldn't be and raise fire-risk meaningfully. This is appliance-side work, replacing a damaged transition duct is our scope, and it's one of the more straightforward repairs we do. If we find damage on a diagnostic call, we'll flag it and quote the replacement." },
  { q: "When does it make sense to repair vs replace damaged vent components?", a: "Vent components are inexpensive enough that replace is almost always the right call when something is actually damaged. A transition duct runs $20–60 in parts; a lint-trap housing $30–80; a booster fan $80–200. The labor to assess and clean a damaged component frequently approaches the cost of just installing a new one, and a damaged duct or housing increases fire risk. The 'replace vs repair' question for vent work is really about whether the symptom is actually a damaged component (replace) vs lint accumulation (cleaning service)." },
  { q: "Do you service commercial or multi-unit building dryer vents?", a: "No, residential single-family, condo, apartment, and ADU installations only. Commercial laundromat vent systems, multi-unit apartment building shared-venting systems, commercial-plant dryer venting, and fire-code-compliance certification work are specialized scopes with different equipment, different parts channels, and different safety-code requirements. The $89 residential diagnostic on this page applies to residential-spec dryer installations only. For commercial dryer venting, contact a commercial HVAC or commercial laundry service provider." }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "@id": canonical + "#service",
    "serviceType": "Appliance-Side Dryer Vent Repair",
    "name": "Dryer Vent Repair, Same Day Appliance Repair",
    "url": canonical,
    "description": "Same-day appliance-side dryer vent repair across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties, transition duct replacement, lint-trap housing replacement, booster fan replacement, exterior vent-flap service. LIMITED-SCOPE: full home vent-system cleaning referred to cleaning specialists. $89 residential diagnostic, applied toward repair.",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "LocalBusiness",
      "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair",
      "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/",
      "telephone": phone,
      "priceRange": "$$",
      "openingHoursSpecification": [
        { "@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Saturday"], "opens": "08:00", "closes": "20:00" },
        { "@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": "Sunday", "opens": "00:00", "closes": "00:00" }
      ]
    },
    "areaServed": [
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Los Angeles County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Orange County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Ventura County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"San Bernardino County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Riverside County"}
    ],
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, applied toward repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Services", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Dryer Vent Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>

