        <h3>Appliance-side repair problem</h3>
        <p>A specific component has failed or is damaged, and the fix is a component replacement rather than a cleaning pass.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Transition duct is visibly crushed, torn, or disconnected</li>
          <li>Lint-trap housing is cracked or damaged</li>
          <li>Booster fan has stopped working</li>
          <li>Exterior vent-flap is stuck or broken (accessible from ground level)</li>
          <li>Diagnostic call needed, is this a dryer problem or vent problem?</li>
          <li>Dryer cycle times suddenly longer + you want the appliance-side portion checked</li>
          <li>Fire-risk review of appliance-side vent after inherited or purchased home</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="choose-card specialist">
        <div class="choose-badge badge-spec">Call cleaning specialist when</div>
        <h3>Home-vent-system cleaning job</h3>
        <p>The problem is lint accumulation in the long run of the vent system, or work requires equipment and access we don't have.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Vent run is long (20+ feet) and has not been cleaned in years</li>
          <li>Routine annual or biennial preventive vent cleaning</li>
          <li>Roof-cap termination needs cleaning or replacement</li>
          <li>Multi-story apartment building shared-vent system</li>
          <li>Fire-code compliance inspection and certification</li>
          <li>Second-story or roof-access exterior termination work</li>
          <li>Commercial laundromat, multi-unit, or commercial-plant venting</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p style="margin-top:28px; font-size:0.92rem; color:#aaa; line-height:1.7; text-align:center;">Not sure which you need? The $89 residential diagnostic covers that question. We tell you honestly whether the job is within our scope or genuinely a cleaning specialist's job, and we refer accordingly.</p>
  </div>
</section>

